            <p>
     EXPORTATION OF LIVE CATTLE. 
     <lb/>
            </p>
   
            <p>
     Mr. MULOCK asked, What was the total 
     <lb/>
     number and value of live cattle exported to 
     <lb/>
     the United Kingdom in the calendar years 
     <lb/>
     1890, 1891, 1892, and 1893 ? 
     <lb/>
            </p>
   
            <p>
     Mr. WALLACE. In 1890 there were 
     <lb/>
     104,133 live cattle exported to the United 
     <lb/>
     Kingdom, of the value of $8,114,145 ; in 1891, 
     <lb/>
     99,967, of the value of $7,381,284 ; in 1892, 
     <lb/>
     93,206, of the value of $6,920,748m; in 1893, 
     <lb/>
     89,572, of the value of $6,799,638, or a total 
     <lb/>
     during the four years of 386,878, of the value 
     <lb/>
     of $29,215,815. 
     <lb/>
            </p>
   
