            <head rendition="simple:centre">
     THE NORTH-WEST SCHOOL QUESTION. 
     <lb/>
            </head>
   
            <p>
     <persName ref="pers:BRUN1">Mr. BRUNEAU</persName> (for Mr. Tarte) asked, 
     <lb/>
     Whether the Government or any of its mem<lb break="no"/>bers have, since the opening of Parliament. 
     <lb/>
     conferred with Lieutenant-Governor Mac<lb break="no"/>kintosh and Mr. Haultain, with reference to 
     <lb/>
     the school question and to the recommend<lb break="no"/>ations made to the Executive of the Terri<lb break="no"/>tories by the Dominion Cabinet ? Have the 
     <lb/>
     Government received from Lieutenant-Gov<lb break="no"/>ernor Mackintosh a favourable answer as to 
     <lb/>
     the said recommendations ? 
     <lb/>
            </p>
   
            <p>
     <persName ref="pers:THOM21">Sir JOHN THOMPSON</persName>. The answer to 
     <lb/>
     the first branch of the question is Yes, and 
     <lb/>
     to the second branch, we have not received 
     <lb/>
     any answer from the Lieutenant-Governor 
     <lb/>
     of the Territories to the recommendations 
     <lb/>
     made by the Order in Council. 
     <lb/>
            </p>
   
   
